<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1324,363,1310]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,518,723,749]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Range extension</emphasis>
: For the Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[722,814,724,750]" name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, some species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1145,1259,724,749]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bodotriidae" genus="Cyclaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1145,1259,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cyclaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been reported from South Florida estuaries (
<bibRefCitation author="Santos" box="[780,1051,764,790]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Santos, S. L. &amp; Simon, J. L. (1980) Response of soft-bottom benthos to annual catastrophic disturbance in a South Florida estuary. Marine Ecology Progress Series, 3 (4), 347 - 355." type="journal article" year="1980">
Santos &amp; Simon, 
<number box="[988,1051,764,790]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), the northeastern shelf (
<bibRefCitation author="Omholt" box="[272,558,804,830]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Omholt, P. E. &amp; Heard, R. W. (1982) Cyclaspis bacescui, new species (Cumacea: Bodotriidae) from the Eastern Gulf of Mexico. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 2 (1), 120 - 129." type="journal article" year="1982">
Omholt &amp; 
<collectingCountry box="[406,481,804,830]" name="Heard Island and McDonald Islands" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Heard</collectingCountry>
, 
<number box="[495,558,804,830]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), Perdido Key, Florida (
<bibRefCitation author="Rakocinski" box="[850,1141,804,830]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Rakocinski, C. F., R. W. Heard, S. E. LeCroy, J. A. McLelland and T. Simons (1993) Seaward change and zonation of the sandy-shore macrofauna at Perdido Key, Florida, U. S. A. Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science 36, 81 - 104." type="journal article" year="1993">
Rakocinski, 
<emphasis box="[1000,1062,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[1079,1141,804,830]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rakocinski" box="[1156,1216,804,830]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Rakocinski, C. F., R. W. Heard, S. E. LeCroy, J. A. McLelland and T. Simons (1996) Responses by macrobenthic assemblages to extensive beach restoration at Perdido Key, Florida, U. S. A. Journal of Coastal Research 12 (1), 326 - 353." type="journal article" year="1996">
<number box="[1156,1216,804,830]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and the Mobile Bay estuarine system, Alabama (
<bibRefCitation author="Modlin" box="[762,1078,844,870]" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" refString="Modlin, R. F. &amp; Dardeau, M. (1987) Seasonal and spatial distribution of cumaceans in the Mobile Bay estuarine system, Alabama .. Estuaries, 10 (4), 291 - 297." type="journal article" year="1987">
Modlin &amp; Dardeau, 
<number box="[1015,1078,844,870]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1987.0">1987</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The record of this genus at CV inlet, Veracruz State, extends its geographic distribution from Quintana Roo and the Mexican Caribbean (
<bibRefCitation author="Markham" box="[600,855,924,950]" pageId="8" pageNumber="14" refString="Markham, J. C., Donath, F. E. Villalobos, J. L. &amp; Diaz, A. C. (1990) Notes on the shallow-water marine Crustacea of the Caribbean coast of Quintana Roo, Mexico. Anales del Instituto de Biologia, Serie Zoologia, 61 (3), 405 - 446." type="journal article" year="1990">
Markham 
<emphasis box="[723,781,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[795,855,924,950]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) into the southwestern Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[1219,1312,924,950]" name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
